wikipedia_page.main: Frances Mary Slaap (born 25 June 1941) is a British athlete. She competed in the women's high jump at the 1960 Summer Olympics and the 1964 Summer Olympics. She also represented England in the 80 metres hurdles and high jump at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Perth, Western Australia.
